en_71309_0	Minimum fine imposed on seven traffic rules violation offences has increased up to 25,000 rupees.
en_71309_1	Ministry of Transport and Civil Aviation states that the relevant gazette has already been issued.
en_71309_2	The amended fines will be presented in Parliament and turned to be a law.
en_71309_3	Accordingly the Act of Motor Vehicle transportation will be updated.
en_71309_4	The decision to increase the fine was taken by a committee of five experts appointed by the President.
en_71309_5	The new amendment will be in effect for offences ; driving without a valid driving license, letting people who do not possess a driving license driving, driving vehicles under the influence of alcohol or drugs, entering a vehicle into railway line carelessly, driving an uninsured vehicle, driving flouting speed limits and overtaking vehicles from the left.
